    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.57a"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">57</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <salute><hi rend="caps">DEAR  EPIC POET</hi>,</salute></opener> <p>some time ago, I wrote you and enclosed stamped env. asking you where I could buy an autographed copy of your collected poems, such as you read from at the Chaparral meeting at Emporia where I met you and Mrs. Neihardt.</p>
                
                <p>I am afraid you did not get the letter.</p>
                
                <p>With help of Margarette Ball Dickson and Mildred Nye Dewey and others of the Chaparral staff, I am acting o<del>g</del><add>r</add>ganizer of <hi rend="caps">MISSOURI CHAPARRAL STATE GROUP</hi>. We are all so anxious for you to be <hi rend="caps">POET LAUREATE</hi>.</p>
                
                <note type="authorial"><unclear/></note>
                
                <p>If you are ill will you have some one drop me a line please. Mrs. Dickson thinks that may be the case instead of my letter's being lost.</p>
                
                <ab type="return">
                    Viola Gardner, <add><unclear>Acting</unclear></add> Regent 
                    <lb/>
                    Missouri Chaparral Poets 
                    <lb/>
                    3815 Mercier, <hi rend="caps">K.C.</hi>, Mo.
                </ab>
                    
                <ab type="postmark">
                    KANSAS CITY 
                    MAR 8 
                    8 PM 
                    1959
                    12 MO.
                
                    AT EASTER
                    HELP
                    CRIPPLED CHI<unclear>LDREN</unclear>
                </ab>
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>3 Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>U.S. POSTAGE 3Â¢
                    IN GOD WE TRUST
                    LIBERTY</p>
                </figure>
                
                A Personal Mailing Card
                
                <ab type="address">
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine><hi rend="caps">SKYRIM</hi> Route #6</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia Mo.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </ab>
                
                <note type="recipient">ansd</note>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
